The paper deals with a machine learning problem involving bandit algorithms, which is a subfield of reinforcement learning. The use of combinatorial bandits and the focus on full-bandit feedback suggest that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of efficient sampling schemes and lower bounds, which are common topics in the subfields of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses regret minimization, which is a topic in the subfield of cs.GT (Game Theory). Finally, the use of Hadamard matrices suggests that the paper may also be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory).
